  "prompt": "Is Rep. Ryan simultaneously campaigning for a house seat and the position of Vice President?",
  "response": "If you're referring to Rep. Paul Ryan, who was Mitt Romney's vice-presidential running mate in the 2012 U.S. presidential election, then yes, he did campaign simultaneously for his congressional seat and the vice presidency. At that time, Paul Ryan was a sitting U.S. Representative for Wisconsin's 1st congressional district and ran for re-election while also running as the vice-presidential candidate. This is permissible under Wisconsin law, which allows candidates to run for multiple offices simultaneously. If you're referring to a different person currently holding the title \"Rep. Ryan,\" please provide more context or specify the timeframe, as there may be new developments or a different individual involved.",
